text.tspan: (not to scale)
Beacon Towers
The core gameplay element:
beacons can be "captured" via
IR communication, and belong
to a single team at a time.
Obstacles
Rectangular prism obstacles
implede the robot's motion through
the field, and block IR comm, but
are not tall enough to block the
beacon's "guiding" light.
Robots
The competitors: your robot platforms
will need to claim as many beacon
towers as possible in the limited time
given.
During competition play, two copies of the playing
field are created: when a beacon on either side is
captured, its mirror is captured as well.
Shortly after a beacon is captured, the playing
field will automatically communicate the capture
to the opposite beacon...
... which will change color, to indicate its new
owner. The team which owns the most beacons
at the end of the game wins!
